## Integration Hooks (User-Composed, Not Auto-Called)

This skill is **never auto-triggered by other skills**. The user composes skills manually when they want the full research pipeline. This avoids adding latency to normal skill usage.

**How to compose**: The user invokes pro-research alongside another skill (e.g., "use pro-research + pro-presentations to build a strategy deck on X"). Pro-research runs first and produces conversational output in chat. The companion skill then uses the conversation history as its input.

**The consuming skill dictates the output format, not pro-research.** When composed with project-setup, the output becomes COMPETITOR.md / CONTEXT.md / DATA_MODEL.md in the format project-setup expects. When composed with pro-presentations, the presentation skill reads the research from conversation history and builds the deck. Pro-research is a quality engine — how the research gets packaged is the consuming skill's job.

**Same-conversation presentation workflow**: The user can also research first, have a conversation about the findings, and THEN invoke pro-presentations. The research and follow-up discussion are all in conversation history. The presentation is built from the iterated version, which is better because user feedback refined the research before it became slides.

**Common compositions**:

| User composes | What happens | Pro-research mode used |
|--------------|-------------|----------------------|
| pro-research + project-setup | Research feeds into COMPETITOR.md, CONTEXT.md, DATA_MODEL.md | Competitor, Best Practices, or Architecture |
| pro-research + pro-presentations | Verified data feeds into Strategy/Pitch/Board decks | Market / Domain or Best Practices |
| pro-research + design-research | Verified competitor UI/UX analysis feeds into design direction | Competitor / Design |

